This paper deals with the capacity of interference channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on one-sided interference channels, which are a type of networked communication system (cs.NI). The paper also discusses fading statistics, which are relevant to wireless communication systems (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents outer bounds and sub-classes, which are concepts commonly used in optimization and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the capacity of communication channels, which is a topic in computer engineering (cs.CE).
